#: index.docbook:26
msgid	"Introduction"
msgstr	""

#: index.docbook:29
msgid	"These two modules work together to control what happens when a "
	"pre-determined low battery condition occurs. There are two of them, "
	"so you can set a warning for when time is getting close, and "
	"something more desperate for the last minute save or suspend."
msgstr	""

#: index.docbook:34
msgid	"The laptop modules require the correct installation of the apm "
	"modules. For more information see the section entitled <link "
	"linkend=\"laptop\">Laptop Information</link>."
msgstr	""

#: index.docbook:39
msgid	"<title>Use</title>"
msgstr	""

#: index.docbook:41
msgid	"Low trigger"
msgstr	""

#: index.docbook:43
msgid	"This field specifies at which point the battery low state is "
	"detected - it is the number of minutes left (according to APM) in "
	"your batteries. When this number is crossed the low state is "
	"triggered and one or more of the following things will occur"
msgstr	""

#: index.docbook:48
msgid	"Run Command"
msgstr	""

#: index.docbook:48
msgid	"This is a shell command that will be executed when the battery low "
	"is detected. By default, this is turned off."
msgstr	""

#: index.docbook:48
msgid	"Play Sound"
msgstr	""

#: index.docbook:48
msgid	"This specifies a sound to play when battery low is detected. As of "
	"this version, it will only play .wav files. Simply specify the path "
	"to the file to have it played. By default, this is turned off."
msgstr	""

#: index.docbook:48
msgid	"System Beep"
msgstr	""

#: index.docbook:48
msgid	"Enabling this will cause the battery monitor to beep whenever the "
	"battery level drops below the preset value. This is probably the "
	"least intrusive, yet still active, method of alerting the user that "
	"the battery is low. By default, this is on."
msgstr	""

#: index.docbook:48
msgid	"Notify"
msgstr	""

#: index.docbook:48
msgid	"Enabling this will cause Battery to popup a window when the battery "
	"becomes low."
msgstr	""

#: index.docbook:48
msgid	"Suspend"
msgstr	""

#: index.docbook:48
msgid	"If you have set up <filename>/usr/bin/apm</filename> to be run "
	"setuid (see the instructions for the \"Power\" panel) then this "
	"check box will appear - if checked it will cause your computer to be "
	"put into \"Suspend\" mode."
msgstr	""

#: index.docbook:48
msgid	"Standby"
msgstr	""

#: index.docbook:48
msgid	"Like \"Suspend\" above, but it puts your computer into \"Standby\" "
	"mode."
msgstr	""

